A table flew across the bar, smashing into some poor frequenter. Quake
raised his fist again, and brought it down, narrowly missing Jagged, and
smashing another table into dust. "You should have stayed out kid." He
threatened, as Jagged kept trying to move away. Swing after swing went
over his head, to his side, narrowly missing, until he was caught
straight in the gut by a kick, followed up by a metal cracking upercut,
which sent him flying into a wall. Quake moved in for the kill. "Yeah,
this is it." He said. He knew it was nothing like the action a war
provides, but it would have to do. He cupped the back of Jagged's head
with one hand, and pulled it forward a little bit, as he drove his fist
straight into his enemies face. Metal crunched, and gave to the strength
of the blow. He stood up, and put his foot on Jagged's throat, getting a
good look at his crushed face. Jagged looked up, through cracked optic
sensors, at a real bad Decepticon, and saw his short pointless life
flash before his eyes.

"Come on Quake, he's just a kid." Slugslinger said from over at a stool. 

"Nunh unh. He's a loud mouth punk, i've dealt with him before. He sure
can't back up his words though." he put pressure on to Jagged's throat,
watching him squirm for gas exchange. He was to busy laughing to notice
the room becoming more hazy, and heavier than just a bit of foul oil
being burned.
